reviews.text: We haven't been here for years, so sorry that we haven't because the food and service were both excellent with live music! Honestly, really enjoyed dinner here, the pork neck was melt in your mouth delicious, the vegetables crisp and well cooked, Tom yum soup and salted fish rice were all really good. Clean and comfortable, it's not the Ritz but it is a lot more accessible...

Outdoor (rare in HK) good food, easy parking and not inside busy city. But it is a cheap place - layout terrible, furniture cheap and old. Nothing nice around the restaurant. And the prices are very high!
Relaxing place for drinks

I have been a customer of Sai Sha Cafe since 2006 and the level or service, food and customer service is consistently outstanding and is reasonably priced. The menu is both in English and Chinese, and most of the staff speak English. Easily accessible by public transport and there is a car park area for customers who have driven.

Very disappointing when we went there for some snack and drinks. It's basically Thai restaurant with prices that match a 5-star hotel. Ordinary drink like coffee is $44 and up. We asked for a snack combo and it is $220 for about 10 pieces of snacks. Compulsory dry squid, nuts at $14 per dish or they charge you $8 for each glass of water! That's extortion!
One star is for the nice waitress service.

reviews.text: 沿馬鞍山西沙路入西貢，會經過西沙路西澳村、西沙荼座、泥涌村等。左面有神學院、泥涌海灘、和泥涌舊村等。泥涌位馬鞍山山腳，附近泥涌海灘景色怡人，有紅樹林和石橋的遺蹟，在日落的時段更顕出這處的美麗。也是放風箏的好去處。
